Adriene, thank you so much for this beautiful practice. I am really working on personal discipline now that the summer is winding down. Really committing to my yoga practice is something really important to me that I want to focus the next month on. Adriene, thank you again for doing what you do. A couple of months ago, your videos got me into a routine of yoga and a body transformation where for the first time in my life I was exercising regularly and getting fit in a healthy way. I was gaining muscle and feeling lean and strong and confident. It started to decline when I worked overnight shifts for two weeks straight due to understaffing at work. It got really bad after a month in Europe (not that that's something to complain about!), but my routine, diet, fitness were all totally thrown off. After returning, I went to an uncomfortable environment and did not properly care for myself especially when I should have paid attention to my sensitivity to jetlag. I have been dehydrated, depressed, overeating, fatigued, and feeling terrible about my weight gain for the past two weeks. Today I wanted to slowly ease back into exercise, starting with yoga. I first searched for new videos, because I knew I was so familiar with yours, I figured something new was needed. But I found that you made a new series, I thought that would be good to follow. Played this video and your voice and method and reassurances made me feel so good and hopeful...I'm just so grateful to have your videos for guidance and I'm so excited to know where to turn when I need healing or change. Thank you, looking forward to continuing my practice with you!

I'm starting this today, I finished yoga camp yesterday and 30days before that. Yesterday was hard for me. I was getting frustrated in the simple poses and questioning my daily commitment. 

Backstory, I have a fully torn ACL and a tear in my meniscus, an injury that forced me to retire 3 years ago from the only physical exercise I ever wanted to do. Roller Derby. Long story short, after 3years of no activity, I found this channel in May and I've been GLOWING since. 

Back to yesterday, I was upset. Maybe it was the silence of the last day, maybe I wasn't mentally there. I don't know but I fought against the practice. I didn't stop, I QUIT. I quit thinking about how I was letting myself down and told myself it was just an off day, but I wasn't fully convinced. THEN IT HAPPENED! Adriene moved into crow pose. Crow is the difficult pose I've chosen to work towards. and I DID IT! I didn't even try that hard, my body did the work. I almost cried but instead let out a squeak of pure joy. And then fell over.

I'm here now 24(ish) hours later. I'm ready to revolt against my negative thoughts and I can't wait to see when I am in another 30days.  

THANK YOU ADRIENE!!!!!!!!! 

Ps. I hope this, my first ever, youtube comment helps someone else push a little bit further in their practice. 
Don't give up, give in!
